# Localization & RTL Guide

## Supported Languages

- **Arabic (ar)** - RTL (Right-to-Left) - Default
- **English (en)** - LTR (Left-to-Right)

---

## Using AppLocalizations

### Required Import

```dart
import 'package:yuser_hr_app/l10n/app_localizations.dart';
```

### Basic Usage

```dart
// ✅ Correct - Always use AppLocalizations
Text(AppLocalizations.of(context)!.welcome)
Text(AppLocalizations.of(context)!.errorOccurred)

// ❌ Wrong - Never hardcode strings
Text('Welcome')
Text('Error occurred')
```

### In Widgets

```dart
class MyWidget extends ConsumerWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context, WidgetRef ref) {
    final l10n = AppLocalizations.of(context)!;
    
    return Column(
      children: [
        Text(l10n.welcome),
        Text(l10n.loginTitle),
        ElevatedButton(
          onPressed: () {},
          child: Text(l10n.submit),
        ),
      ],
    );
  }
}
```

