## RTL-Aware Properties

### ⚠️ CRITICAL: Never Use left/right

**Always use `start`/`end` instead of `left`/`right`:**

### EdgeInsets

```dart
// ❌ Wrong
EdgeInsets.only(left: 16, right: 8)
EdgeInsets.fromLTRB(16, 0, 8, 0)

// ✅ Correct
EdgeInsetsDirectional.only(start: 16, end: 8)
EdgeInsetsDirectional.fromSTEB(16, 0, 8, 0)
```

### Alignment

```dart
// ❌ Wrong
Alignment.centerLeft
Alignment.topRight
CrossAxisAlignment.start // This is OK

// ✅ Correct
AlignmentDirectional.centerStart
AlignmentDirectional.topEnd
```

### BorderRadius

```dart
// ❌ Wrong
BorderRadius.only(
  topLeft: Radius.circular(8),
  bottomRight: Radius.circular(8),
)

// ✅ Correct
BorderRadiusDirectional.only(
  topStart: Radius.circular(8),
  bottomEnd: Radius.circular(8),
)
```

### Positioned (in Stack)

```dart
// ❌ Wrong
Positioned(left: 16, child: widget)

// ✅ Correct
PositionedDirectional(start: 16, child: widget)
```

### Text Alignment

```dart
// ✅ Correct - Use start/end
Text('Hello', textAlign: TextAlign.start)
Text('Hello', textAlign: TextAlign.end)

// ⚠️ Avoid left/right unless specifically needed
Text('Hello', textAlign: TextAlign.left)  // Only for LTR-only content
```

