## Checking Text Direction

When you need to check direction programmatically:

```dart
final isRTL = Directionality.of(context) == TextDirection.rtl;

// Override direction (use sparingly)
Directionality(
  textDirection: TextDirection.ltr, // Force LTR for specific content
  child: widget,
)
```

---

## Icons in RTL

Most icons flip automatically. To prevent flipping:

```dart
// Icon flips automatically in RTL
Icon(Icons.arrow_forward)  // ✅ Flips correctly

// Prevent icon from flipping
Directionality(
  textDirection: TextDirection.ltr,
  child: Icon(Icons.arrow_forward),  // Won't flip
)
```

---

## Implementation Checklist

When implementing any UI:

- [ ] All user-facing strings use `AppLocalizations`
- [ ] All `left`/`right` converted to `start`/`end`
- [ ] Using `EdgeInsetsDirectional` for directional padding
- [ ] Using `AlignmentDirectional` for directional alignment
- [ ] Using `BorderRadiusDirectional` for directional corners
- [ ] Using `PositionedDirectional` in Stacks
- [ ] Tested in Arabic (RTL)
- [ ] Tested in English (LTR)
- [ ] Icons flip correctly (or prevented where needed)
- [ ] Dates/numbers formatted with `intl`

